        <hl1>Lest We Forget: The Thunderbolt</hl1>
      </hedline>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>In ''Greener Pastures'' (Op-Ed, Feb. 5), Representative Steve Israel lists the ''famous aircraft of World War II'' built on Long Island. He leaves out the best and most famous fighter plane of World War II, the Republic P-47 Thunderbolt, built on Long Island by Republic Aviation.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>In ''Greener Pastures'' (Op-Ed, Feb. 5), Representative Steve Israel lists the ''famous aircraft of World War II'' built on Long Island. He leaves out the best and most famous fighter plane of World War II, the Republic P-47 Thunderbolt, built on Long Island by Republic Aviation.</p>
        <p>Those many P-47 pilots still here on Long Island will cross it off to Mr. Israel's having had a senior moment.</p>
        <p>John Wenzel  Manhasset</p>
      </block>
